Step 1. Calculate Return on Equity (ROE):
• Beginning Owner’s Equity = Paid-in Capital + Beginning Retained Earnings = 13,000,000.00 + 0 = 13,000,000.00
• Ending Owner’s Equity = 14,903,401.82 (given)
• Average Owner’s Equity = (13,000,000.00 + 14,903,401.82) / 2 = 13,951,700.91 (approximately)
• Net Profit = 1,903,401.82 (from income statement)
• ROE = (Net Profit / Average Owner’s Equity) × 100 ≈ (1,903,401.82 / 13,951,700.91) × 100 ≈ 13.64%

Step 2. Calculate Debt to Asset Ratio:
• Total Liabilities = Accounts Payable + Taxes Payable = 381,000.00 + 243,988.48 = 624,988.48
• Total Assets (End) = 15,528,390.30
• Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets ≈ 624,988.48 / 15,528,390.30 ≈ 0.0402, which is about 0.04

Step 3. Calculate Gross Profit Margin:
• Gross Profit = 2,861,769.51 (from income statement)
• Total Revenue = 4,879,769.51
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100 ≈ (2,861,769.51 / 4,879,769.51) × 100 ≈ 58.60%

Thus, the solution in the required format is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Return on Equity (ROE)": "13.64%",
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.04",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "58.60%"
  }
}
